1ï¸âƒ£ What is Redis (in very simple terms)

	Redis is an in-memory data store
	It stores data as key â†’ value
	Super fast (RAM-based)

	Common uses:
		Caching
		Session storage
		Rate limiting
		Queues
		Counters

	Think of Redis like a huge Hash in memory, but with special value types.

		key => value

2ï¸âƒ£ Starting Redis (local)
	Install & start
		redis-server

	Open Redis CLI
		redis-cli


	Youâ€™ll now see:

		127.0.0.1:6379>

3ï¸âƒ£ Redis basics (common to all data types)
	Set a key
	SET mykey "hello"

	Get a key
	GET mykey

	Delete a key
	DEL mykey

	Check if key exists
	EXISTS mykey

	Set expiry (TTL)
	EXPIRE mykey 60     # seconds
	TTL mykey

4ï¸âƒ£ Redis Data Types (MOST IMPORTANT PART)

	Redis does NOT store arbitrary objects.
	It stores specific data types.

	ğŸ”¹ 1. STRING (most basic)
	What it is

	Can store:
	text
	numbers
	JSON
	binary data

	Commands
	SET name "Shubham"
	GET name

	Numbers (counter)
	SET views 10
	INCR views
	INCRBY views 5

	Store JSON (very common)
	SET user:1 '{"id":1,"name":"Alice"}'
	GET user:1


	ğŸ’¡ Redis does not understand JSON â€” itâ€™s just a string.

2. HASH (like Ruby Hash)
	What it is

	Key â†’ multiple fields

	Perfect for objects

	Example: user object
	HSET user:1 id 1 name Alice email alice@test.com

	Read fields
	HGET user:1 name
	HGETALL user:1

	Update field
	HSET user:1 name Bob

	Delete field
	HDEL user:1 email


	ğŸ“Œ Use HASH instead of JSON string when you need partial updates

3. LIST (ordered, allows duplicates)
	What it is

	Like an array / queue

	Order matters

	Push items
	LPUSH tasks "email"
	LPUSH tasks "backup"

	Read items
	LRANGE tasks 0 -1

	Pop items (queue)
	RPOP tasks

	Blocking queue (important)
	BRPOP tasks 0


	ğŸ“Œ Used for job queues, background workers


4. SET (unique values, unordered)
	What it is

	Like Ruby Set

	No duplicates

	Commands
	SADD tags ruby rails redis
	SADD tags ruby
	SMEMBERS tags

	Check membership
	SISMEMBER tags rails

	Set operations
	SINTER set1 set2   # intersection
	SUNION set1 set2   # union


	ğŸ“Œ Used for permissions, tags, feature flags

5. SORTED SET (Set + score)
	What it is

	Like Set, but each value has a score

	Sorted by score

	Example: leaderboard
	ZADD leaderboard 100 alice
	ZADD leaderboard 200 bob
	ZADD leaderboard 150 carol

	Read leaderboard
	ZRANGE leaderboard 0 -1 WITHSCORES
	ZREVRANGE leaderboard 0 -1 WITHSCORES


	ğŸ“Œ Used for ranking, rate limiting, analytics

5ï¸âƒ£ TTL & Expiry (very important)

	Works for all types

	SET session:123 "logged_in"
	EXPIRE session:123 3600
	TTL session:123


	ğŸ“Œ Redis auto-deletes expired keys.


6ï¸âƒ£ Redis vs DB vs Cache

	| Feature       | Redis        | Database  |
	| ------------- | ------------ | --------- |
	| Stored in RAM | âœ…            | âŒ         |
	| Persistent    | âš ï¸ optional  | âœ…         |
	| Query support | âŒ            | âœ…         |
	| Speed         | ğŸš€ very fast | ğŸ¢ slower |


7ï¸âƒ£ Redis from Rails (simple example)
	redis = Redis.new

	redis.set("name", "Shubham")
	redis.get("name")

	redis.hset("user:1", "name", "Alice")
	redis.hgetall("user:1")

8ï¸âƒ£ How Rails.cache uses Redis
	Rails.cache.write("user_1", user)
	Rails.cache.read("user_1")


	Internally:

	Object â†’ Marshal.dump

	Stored as Redis STRING

	Read â†’ Marshal.load

9ï¸âƒ£ Which data type should I use?

	| Use case                | Redis type |
	| ----------------------- | ---------- |
	| Cache whole object      | STRING     |
	| Partial object update   | HASH       |
	| Queue / background jobs | LIST       |
	| Unique items            | SET        |
	| Ranking / scoring       | SORTED SET |


10ï¸âƒ£ Mental model (IMPORTANT)

	Redis is not a database
	Redis is a data-structure server

	Each key has one data type.
